ile being supervised by ctp details tempest engineer responsible for all aspects of the assigned tempest project details senior tempest engineer  ctpii being an established and respected tempest manufacturing and sales company with locations in marylands baltimorewashington corridor and in new hampshire api has the need to grow its tempest testing capabilities level ii certified tempest professionals are needed to play a major role in this growth period the ctpiis must be experienced with testing a wide variety of equipment as well as scheduling and preparing the equipmentundertest eut for testing in accordance with the test plan and current national tempest standards the tasks of this position will be fulfilled at both company facilities and at customer sites throughout the country education andor experience should include a bs degree from a fouryear college or university and  years of related experience andor training or equivalent combination of education and experience secret level security clearance required details us citizenship required for most positions eoeaa mfdv please send resumes and salary history to advanced programs inc  riverwood drive columbia maryland  to the attention of human resources or email to hradvprogramscom serving the united states  all nato countries what is tempest  advanced programs inc what is tempest tempest is the study of electromagnetic emissions from data processing equipment such as computers networking gear and printers such emissions can be collected and processed to reveal information that is being stored processed or displayed this presents the security risk of sensitive andor classified information being unintentionally compromised to adversaries tempest products are created to reduce or eliminate the electromagnetic emissions most information concerning tempest techniques and specifications is classified by the united states government and is not available for general use the national security agency manages the tempest certification programs tcp that consist of three closely related nsa programs the certified tempest products program the certified tempest test services program and the zoned equipment program these programs involve partnerships with industry further information can be found at their site httpwwwnsagovapplicationsiatempestindexcfm tempest levels the usa and nato use different names for similar tempest levels the following table is provided as a useful crossreference serving the united states  all nato countries ﻿ quality  advanced programs inc qualitycompliance apis columbia md and salem nh facilities are iso  certified api® is firmly committed to providing customer satisfaction through superior quality in products and service by delivering on time and meeting or exceeding the customer requirements the management of api® is committed to quality and continual improvement in all areas of the organization working as a team involving all employees api® is committed to a process of continually improving customer satisfaction product quality and the quality management system tim mcmichael director of quality  compliance  tmcmichaeladvprogramscom nsa endorsement for over twenty years api® has been endorsed by the nsa to design build and test tempest equipment api® offers emanation secure versions of current business class computing devices contracts gsa contract vehicle — gsa gsfp nato contract vehicle — ncaboa  about iso  excerpt from iso “iso  specifies requirements for a quality management system where an organization needs to demonstrate its ability to consistently provide product that meets customer and applicable statutory and regulatory requirements and aims to enhance customer satisfaction through the effective application of the system including processes for continual improvement of the system and the assurance of conformity to customer and applicable statutory and regulatory requirements” serving the united states  all nato countries tempest testing  emi testing